    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-18T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="443"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d443">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3268: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-18T19:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1921—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 18—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93. Quo Tai-chi on behalf of Canton Government requests that the Legation point
                    out to the Department that the accumulated Southern customs surpluses were
                    allocated with Peking Government’s consent withdrawal of which is retroactive
                    and <hi rend="italic">ultra vires</hi>, same argument applying to position of
                    the diplomatic body which has recently rejected Peking’s application for these
                    funds. I have no comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
